<br>
Why do I ask this?  Because more and more I see that if you don't belong to one of the very few guilds on the top, there is a very non-existent chance of seeing the end game, gaining epics, etc. (the Blayze incident comes to mind).<br>
<br>
How I would see this would work:<br>
<br>
1)  A guild joins the alliance and lets it be known what their membership and resources are.<br>
2)  A council is formed of the guildmasters of each guild.<br>
3)  A cross guild master list is created for gaining epics based on seniority or whatever scheme the council decides.<br>
4)  A chat channel is opened for all members of the alliance.<br>
<br>
The details would all have to be worked out of course and this just a passing thought without a whole lot of thought being put into it.<br>
any input would be greatly appreciated.<br>
